original: Friden, Anders Lennart Sigfrid, komminister, Trollhättan, f. 27/6/98 i Slöta, Skarab. L, av folkskoll. S. N. F. o. Nanny Lithander. G. 26 m. folkskoll. Märta Janson. Barn: Sven f. 28, Margareta 30. — Studrex. i Skara 18, teol. fil. ex. 21, teol. kand. samt prästv. f. Skara stift 25. V. pastor i Finnerödja 26, kommin. i Älgarås 26-32, kyrkoh. n Västra Ny 32-45, kommin. i Trollhättan sed. 45. I Västra Ny bl. a. ordf. i kyrkostämma o. skolstyr. samt sångled. f. Kyrkosång. vänn. i Linköp. stift, led. av Trollhättans hemb :kör. Hobby: botanik.
translated:
Friden, Anders Lennart Sigfrid, vicar, Trollhättan, born on June 27th, 1898 in Slöta, Skaraborg county, son of a primary school teacher. His mother's name was Nanny Lithander. He married Märta Janson in 1926, who also attended primary school. They have two children: Sven, born in 1928, and Margareta, born in 1930. 

Anders studied at Skara college in 1918, received a degree in theology and philosophy in 1921, and was ordained as a minister in 1925 in the Diocese of Skara. He was an assistant pastor in Finnerödja in 1926, a curate in Älgarås from 1926 to 1932, a vicar in Västra Ny from 1932 to 1945, and a curate in Trollhättan since 1945. While in Västra Ny, he was the chairman of the church meeting and the school committee, and also directed the church choir. He was a member of the church choir association in the Diocese of Linköping. His hobby was botany.
